children.subject: why do u think its a bad idea to take 126 and 127 together? I actually took half of 126 and eecs16b (up to first midterm) a couple semesters ago but dropped out of school due to medical reasons.

I personally would not take both since imo the workload ranking is [127, 126] > [170, 126] > [170, 127]. I think the complexity of 170 is higher than 127 for you (since you have a pretty good background in linear algebra), but having to do both 126 and 127 problem sets weekly sounds like a nightmare.

I think either [16B, 170, 127] or [16B, 170, 126] would be the best courseload. I would not take both 126 and 127 together. Between the two that I mentioned, the first one would probably be easier since 16B and 127 have some overlap (spectral theorem, svd, pca, etc.) and you've already taken Math 110. The other one is also doable, but will be harder since there is less overlap.
